.TH "drm_format_info_min_pitch" 9 "drm_format_info_min_pitch" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_format_info_min_pitch \- computes the minimum required pitch in bytes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "uint64_t" drm_format_info_min_pitch
.BI "(const struct drm_format_info *info "  ","
.BI "int plane "  ","
.BI "unsigned int buffer_width "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
pixel format info
.IP "plane" 12
plane index
.IP "buffer_width" 12
buffer width in pixels
.SH "RETURN"
The minimum required pitch in bytes for a buffer by taking into consideration
the pixel format information and the buffer width.
